On [[14 June]] [[1973]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] wrote '''a ''[[Wikipedia:Procuration|per procurationem]]'' [[Letters not published in The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien|letter]] to Bruce Charlton'''.<ref name=Notion>{{webcite|author=Bruce Charlton|articleurl=http://notionclubpapers.blogspot.com/2013/10/a-previously-unpublished-letter-from.html|articlename=A previously unpublished letter from JRR Tolkien - 14 June 1973|dated=5 October 2013|website=[http://notionclubpapers.blogspot.com Notionclubpapers.blogspot.com]|accessed=16 October 2012}}</ref>

==Excerpt==
{{blockquote|Dear Mr Charlton<br/><br/>Thank you very much for your kind letter. I am delighted that my books have given you pleasure.<br/><br/>THE SILMARILLION is far from complete and I have not looked at it for some considerable time. Therefore I regret that I cannot predict when it will see the light of day.<br/><br/>Yours sincerely, <br/><br/>pp. JRR Tolkien<br/><br/>[initials] MJH<ref name=Notion/>}}

